                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well, the reason your summations hold no water is : Gandalf was not a man.  He did not have to die to not be a man.  He NEVER was a man.  At this particular time in the history of middle earth, he had been around as "Gandalf" for thousands of years.  
<br />

<br />
If you had read the books, along with Tolkien's other writings, you would know that Gandalf was a Maeri (sp?), of the same ilk as Morgoth, who was Sauron's master and the bane of middle-earth in the First Age I believe it was.  I could be wrong on this, I have not read the Silmarillion in 20 years, but I think I got my facts straight.
<br />

<br />
I can see how seeing the movies without reading the books would have led you to your conclusions though.  I think the biggest problem with this series of movies was that Peter Jackson made it particularly for the people that had been fans of the book.  I think he assumes the viewers of the movie already know the story.  Maybe this was done on a subconsious level.  Maybe since he and his fellow screenplay writers knew the story, it was easy for them to not worry about things like this, since they already knew what the prophecy of the witch-king meant.  
<br />

<br />
It might have been a good idea for them to let someone who had never read the books read the script to see if it made sense to them.  I don't know if this was done or not, but that is what I would have done.
<br />

<br />
Who can argue with his ways though, the freakin series made like 2.5 billion dollars!!!
<br />

<br />
Anyway, I had always had the impression that the prophecy of "no man" killing the witch-kinig meant no MALE, not human.  After all, Eowyn is a human, she just happens to be female.  Arwen is a woman, she just happens to be an Elf woman.  See what I mean? 
<br />

<br />
My problem with the whole witch-king death was how easily she killed the beast he was riding.  She hacked through his 3 foot wide neck in like 2 strokes.  That was a bit too quick for my tastes.  
<br />

<br />
My favorite of the movies is still the first one.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Dalavon &lt;Dead of Winter&gt;
