                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Guys the fact is the director screwed up the series at this point.  Building the tension for a showdown between Gandolf and the witch king was correct based on the books.  In the book, Gandolf goes to the gates of Minas Tirith and prepares to face the Witch King as they break through.  The witch king enters and Gandolf faces him.  However, before they can battle the Riders of Rohan attack and Pippin comes to Gandolf to tell him of the madness of the Steward of Gondor.  The witch king leaves to take care of the Riders and Gandolf tells the soldiers at the gate to fall back to the next one and he goes with Pippin to save the life of Faramir.  IMO Peter Jackson just didnt get the editing sequence right to show why Gandolf didn't fight the witch king.  Eowyn faces the witch king exactly in the movie as she does in the book with aid of Merridoc.
<br />

<br />
    BTW Gandolf at several points is shown as having equal strength to the wraiths.  As a holder of one of the three hidden rings of the elves he is powerful but always constrained by the need to preserve the powers he has against discovery.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
