                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">A few minor corrections:
<br />
First, Morgoth did not bring the dragons. He had corrupted great eagles into forms now known as dragons. He also corrupted each of the races into soemthing else, ie elves -> orcs ; ents -> trolls, etc. He could corrupt life but could never create life, only Eru could do that.(Although there IS an exception to that  <img src="images/smiles/icon_suspicious.gif" alt="icon_suspicious.gif" border="0" />  )
<br />
Second, Gandalf wasn't one of the leaders of the Istari wizards. Actually he was a late addition to them and was initially the weakest. The other 4 had lost their focus and had begun to accumulate power of their own, thus wandering from their initial focus.
<br />
Third, the reason why Gandalf and the others also didn't go in blasting was that Sauron could locate large uses of magic, and usually hunted down rogue mages of power.
<br />
Also they were sent to advise the races, not spearhead offensives. So it was frowned upon if they used anything besides their knowledge to help the races.
<br />

<br />
There is a TON of stuff out there nowadays about Middle Earth. I would highly recommend reading a few of the books, although the Silmarillion is bit.. ummm.. thick at times while reading.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=247107" target="_blank" class="postlink">Goloth</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.therunes.net/forums/viewtopic.php?t=5628" target="_blank" class="postlink">E61.4/Xg h+ 1.7khp 3.5km ft2 G+&lt;3 e++ o+++ T+ L !H f g+ b- c++ t++ D !X FP-- !E S- FE++ TR- GT--</a> <span style="color: red">RETIRED</span>
