                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">A lot of info was released by Iron Crown Enterprises when they gained rights to release Middle Earth Role Playing from JRR himself.
<br />
They took a lot of the gaps and filled them. So while not technically Tolkein lore, he did approve it. 
<br />
They added a lot of background info for the Istari, the Valar, and the First Age elves, as well as more info on the Numenoreans. As well as more info on the origins of a lot of the races and monsters.
<br />
Unfortunately, they filed for bankruptcy and lost the rights to the ME information when they reformed the company and Christopher opened up rights to gaming in ME to the highest bidder. But you can still find a lot of their source books out there.
<br />

<br />
While I guess for a purist, the information is not written by JRR himself, it was approved by him and fit his vision of Middle Earth. But some cool stories and info available from them  <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=247107" target="_blank" class="postlink">Goloth</a>
<br />
